HEADWORD: Pia mater
<hw>Pi"a ma"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>pia</ets>
(fem. of <ets>pius</ets> tender, kind) + <ets>mater</ets> mother.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The delicate and highly vascular membrane
immediately investing the brain and spinal cord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

